<header class="hero" id="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <p class="kicker reveal visible">A financial thought experiment</p>
    <h1 class="reveal visible">
      What CAGR do you expect from your <span class="muted">natural death?</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-sub reveal visible">
      Term insurance is the only product where extraordinary returns require unfortunate timing.
    </p>
    <div class="scroll-cue reveal visible" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>scroll</span>
      <div class="scroll-cue-line"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<section class="section-pad" id="paradox">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="split-grid reveal">
      <article class="split-card">
        <div class="split-label">Investment</div>
        <p><strong>Rewards survival.</strong> The longer you remain around, the longer compounding has room to work.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="split-card">
        <div class="split-label">Term insurance</div>
        <p><strong>Rewards interruption.</strong> The earlier the payout occurs, the more mathematically attractive the return appears.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="center-thought reveal delay-1">
      <p>Every additional year lived adds another premium while the payout remains fixed. The ratio gets less flattering. The life gets better.</p>
      <p>Longevity is wonderful. Financially inefficient, but wonderful.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-pad" id="calculator">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="kicker">The instrument</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Implied CAGR Calculator</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">Use normal insurance language. Enter cover in lakh or crore. Let the page do the zeros.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calc-wrap">
<form class="form-card card reveal delay-2" id="calc-form" novalidate="">
        <div class="form-grid">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="premium">Annual premium</label>
            <div class="input-shell">
              <span class="prefix">₹</span>
              <input class="form-input" id="premium" type="number" inputmode="numeric" min="1" step="1" placeholder="12000" required="">
            </div>
            <div class="field-hint">Yearly amount paid to the insurer.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="field">
            <label for="cover-amount">Cover amount</label>
            <div class="input-shell">
              <span class="prefix">₹</span>
              <input class="form-input" id="cover-amount" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0.1" step="0.1" placeholder="1" required="">
              <select class="form-select" id="cover-unit" aria-label="Cover unit">
                <option value="100000">Lakh</option>
                <option value="10000000" selected="">Crore</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="field-hint">Example: 1 crore, 50 lakh, 2.5 crore.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="field">
            <label for="current-age">Current age</label>
            <div class="input-shell">
              <input class="form-input" id="current-age" type="number" inputmode="numeric" min="18" max="90" placeholder="30" required="">
              <span class="suffix">yrs</span>
            </div>
            <div class="field-hint">Your age today.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="field">
            <label for="expiry-age">Policy expiry age</label>
            <div class="input-shell">
              <input class="form-input" id="expiry-age" type="number" inputmode="numeric" min="19" max="100" placeholder="65" required="">
              <span class="suffix">yrs</span>
            </div>
            <div class="field-hint">Age when term coverage ends.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="field" id="desired-cagr-field">
            <label for="desired-cagr">Desired CAGR</label>
            <div class="input-shell">
              <input class="form-input" id="desired-cagr" type="number" inputmode="decimal" min="0.1" max="200" step="0.1" placeholder="12">
              <span class="suffix">%</span>
            </div>
            <div class="field-hint">What annualized return are you implicitly asking for?</div>
          </div>
<div class="field-hint">What annualized return are you implicitly asking for?</div>
          </div>
        </form></div>

        <button class="cta" id="calculate-btn" type="submit">Solve for the age</button>
      

      <div class="result" id="result" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
        <div class="result-card card">
          <div class="result-primary" id="result-primary">—</div>
          <span class="result-number mono" id="result-number">—</span>
          <div class="result-secondary" id="result-secondary">—</div>
          <div class="meta-grid" id="meta-grid"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  
</section>

<section class="section-pad" id="curve">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="kicker">The curve</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Survival vs. return</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">This line slopes downward for structural reasons. More life means more premiums. More premiums mean lower implied CAGR.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="graph-card card reveal delay-1">
      <div class="chart-wrap">
        <canvas id="chart" role="img" aria-label="Chart showing implied CAGR declining as age of death increases." width="897" height="1119" style="width: 319px; height: 398px;"></canvas>
      </div>
      <div class="graph-caption">implied annualized CAGR by age of death</div>
      <div class="graph-notes">
        <div class="graph-note"><strong>Earlier death</strong> Higher CAGR.</div>
        <div class="graph-note"><strong>Longer survival</strong> Lower CAGR.</div>
        <div class="graph-note"><strong>The point</strong> Insurance is a hedge, not an asset class.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-pad" id="education">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="kicker">A better interpretation</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Term insurance is an expense worth expensing on</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">The right mental model is not “What return did I get?” The right question is “What financial damage did I prevent for people who depend on me?”</p>
    </div>

    <div class="edu-grid">
      <article class="edu-card reveal delay-1">
        <h3>Not all money spent needs to compound</h3>
        <p>Rent, antivirus, backups, legal compliance, and fire extinguishers are all deliberate expenses. Their value is highest when the catastrophe never arrives.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="edu-card reveal delay-2">
        <h3>What you are actually buying</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Income continuity for dependents.</li>
          <li>Debt protection during vulnerable years.</li>
          <li>Time for your family to reorganize after interruption.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="edu-card reveal delay-3">
        <h3>The category error</h3>
        <p>If the best personal outcome is that the product never pays out, then it should not be evaluated like equity, real estate, or a fixed-income instrument.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-pad" id="closing">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <blockquote class="closing-quote reveal">Buy term insurance to protect continuity. Not to optimize mortality.</blockquote>
    <p class="closing-copy reveal delay-1">The payout is not the aspiration. The peace of mind is. If the policy expires unused, the financial return was poor and the human outcome was excellent.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<footer class="footer">
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <span>Natural Death CAGR · 2026</span>
    <span>FV = P × [((1+r)^n − 1) / r]</span>
  </div>
</footer>




